t: “Dominion*pn and awe belong to Him Who*ln establishes peace in His heights.
Is*ln there any number to His troops? And*ln upon whom does His light not rise?
How*ln then can a man be just with God? Or*ln how can he be clean who is born of woman?
If*ln even the moon has no brightness And*ln the stars are not pure in His sight,
How*ln much less man, that*i maggot, And*ln the son of man, that*i worm!”
